Jenna Etheridge, News24The injured Lion's Head hiker was extracted by helicopter. (Supplied: Netcare911) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cape Town &ndash; A hiker was injured after slipping and falling approximately 20m down Lion's Head in Cape Town on Thursday morning, said Wilderness Search and Rescue (WSAR)."He was able to prevent himself from falling further by grabbing onto bushes and landed up slipping about 20m to 30m down," said WSAR spokesperson Johann Marais.The man, in his late 30s, was in considerable pain when the medics got to him. He sustained back injuries.He was extricated by helicopter and rushed to a nearby hospital by ambulance.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.